delinquent taxes, and transitioned her office to online delinquent tax sales as well as to e-filing
and permanent digital storage of all Chancery and Probate Court records for Hamblen County;
and
WHEREAS, a leader in her profession, Ms. Jones-Terry has been a member of the State
Court Clerks' Association of Tennessee since 1995, serving as state treasurer (1996-2001);
East Tennessee secretary, vice president, and president (2002-2005); state president-elect
(2005-2006); state president (2006-2007); and state secretary (2008-2010, 2018-2019); and
WHEREAS, she brought her teaching background to the State Court Clerks' Association
of Tennessee, streamlining professional education courses so clerks could learn more in a
single session and forming a committee to rework the general manual for clerks; and
WHEREAS, she was also a member of the County Officials Association of Tennessee
from 1995 to 2025, where she served numerous terms on the Board of Directors and on various
committees, including the Charity Focus Committee, which she served as clerk (2017-2018) and
chair and clerk (2019-2025); and
WHEREAS, Ms. Jones-Terry has been duly honored for her good work over the years;
she was named the State Court Clerks' Association of Tennessee's Clerk of the Year in 2003,
and in 2019, the County Officials Association of Tennessee named her Court Clerk of the Year;
and
WHEREAS, Kathy Jones-Terry exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and
community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout her illustrious tenure as Hamblen County Chancery and Probate
Court Clerk and Master, Ms. Jones-Terry has distinguished herself as a public-spirited citizen of
the highest order, winning the respect and admiration of her colleagues and the people she has
so ably served; now, therefore,
